HEADWORD: Brother-in-law
<hw>Broth"er-in-law`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Brothers-in-law</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<def>The brother of one's husband or wife; also, the husband of one's
sister; sometimes, the husband of one's wife's sister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brotherliness</ent>⟦br⟧
